    "The first part (red) tracks the weight plot to focus on relevant features, while the second part (green) introduces high-capacity output gates.",
    "At the core of both is a pool operation that enables smooth attention tracking and flexible output gating.",
    "To make full use of spatial features in the video, Li et al. (2018b) proposed the VideoLSTM model in 2016.",
    "VideoLSTM uses convolution and action-based attention mechanisms to obtain spatial correlation and action-based attention graphs in video frames.",
    "In 2021, Muhammad et al. (2021) proposed an attentional mechanism based on bidirectional long-and short-term memory, which includes a dilated convolution neural network (DCNN)."
